If you have the following markup (where "I" indicates the cursor): 

{code}
<li>
   <p>foo bar <span>baz boo I</span></p>
</li>
{code}

Hitting enter produces another paragraph _rather than a new list item_ (which is what is expected). 

By default, we don't normally wrap the contents of list items in a paragraph tag. We do wrap contents when a user inserts a macro body placeholder inside a list item. 

It's also possible to get a P inside an LI if you copy and paste from other RTE's (like evernote). 

P is a legal element to have inside an LI.

