{noformat}
http://localhost/display/TST/Test+Page?focusedCommentId=1933325#comment-1933325
{noformat}
The link works, but when editing you can see the source is like:
{noformat}
<a 
  data-mce-href="http://localhost:8080/confluence/display/TST2/Funny%21+Page+%3C+title+page+%3A+%29+is+funny?focusedCommentId=1933325#comment-1933325" 
  href="http://localhost:8080/confluence/display/TST2/Funny%21+Page+%3C+title+page+%3A+%29+is+funny?focusedCommentId=1933325#comment-1933325"
>
    Re: Funny! Page < title page : ) is funny
</a>
{noformat}
No data attributes indicating the comment id or the page the comment is attached to. No data-linked-resource-default-alias. If the page title is changed, the link will break and the link text will be incorrect.

This seems like a regression but I can't find a test that's failing for it ;)

